gomodel:SYNGO_4140  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 5 illustrates the presence of this receptor in the neuromuscular synapse. A high co-localization between the syntaxin, used as nerve terminal marker, and p75NTR indicates likelihood of nerve terminal localization (Fig. 5A).. Experimental description: Experiments were performed on the Levator auris longus (LAL) muscle of adult Sprague-Dawley rats (30-40 days post-natal; Criffa, Barcelona, Spain)." , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" ;
